To the "Condemn a season they haven't even seen yet" Community with the "Wah wah it looks like it's just gonna be a normal sci fi dystopian future show now.. wah wah no hats and horses..." have the writers proven nothing by now?

You all that love banging on about shows switching it up be the same furiously smashing keys in comments if they remain the same.

Would it be interesting if they had gone with this that and the third idea from all your fan fiction fantasies of what Season 2 "should" have been and 3 "should" be going forward? Maybe yeah!

Hey, while we're at it- hows about "100 Years War", "Nubian", or "Prehistoric" Worlds? Why tf not.

But this is the way they're going- bearing in mind that it's just the trailer and we don't know just where we'll end up .

Until such time, put in as much work as the Westworld team has done in bringing such a grand project to the table, or Stfu and let the thing begin at least?, sheesh.
